rComments: Definitely knows his stuff, also very accessible and a cool guy.
I took two of his courses.  He's an absolutely brilliant Prof!  Lectures are fun and very educational.  He talks really fast, but slows down if you ask him to.

Incredibly learned and super nice.  Genuinely cares about his students.  The downside is that he talks way too fast.  He also doesn't post much info online, because "it's unfair for students who skip class get the same slides".  But he'll help you out if you go to office hours.
Doesn't always give clear instructions, always gives very short readings and bonus questions on the mid term and final. Only posts important terms but doesn't give any other information with them
